---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Pool Builders Mudgeeraba | Acreage Freeform Concrete | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Swimming pool builders for Mudgeeraba — acreage freeform concrete pools, hinterland granite-soil engineering, large pavilion-paired pools. QBCC-licensed. Free quote.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://goldcoastpoolbuilders.com.au/mudgeeraba/">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Mudgeeraba &middot; Tallai &middot; Worongary &middot; Gold Coast hinterland</span>
      <h1>Pool builders in <span class="accent">Mudgeeraba</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Mudgeeraba is the start of the Gold Coast hinterland. Acreage blocks
        1&ndash;5 hectares, granite-based hinterland soil rather than coastal
        sand, mature gardens, mountain views over the Numinbah Valley and
        Springbrook range. Pools here are usually large freeform concrete with
        a paired alfresco pavilion or pool house &mdash; the whole &ldquo;outdoor
        living estate&rdquo; package.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free on-site quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Mudgeeraba</span>
      <h2>The Mudgeeraba pool story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Hinterland granite soil = different engineering.</h3>
        <p>
          Mudgeeraba and the wider Gold Coast hinterland sit on
          <strong>weathered granite + clay-loam</strong>, not coastal sand or
          alluvial silt. That changes the excavation and structural engineering.
          Concrete shotcrete shell construction is fine. Fibreglass shells need
          a careful bedding-sand layer because granite chunks can puncture a
          shell that&rsquo;s direct-placed on the cut. Excavation often hits
          weathered rock at 1.5&ndash;2.5m &mdash; rock-breaker hire adds
          $2K&ndash;$5K depending on extent.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Acreage = freeform, not rectangular.</h3>
        <p>
          On a 350m&sup2; Mermaid Beach block, rectangular and tight is the
          only option. On a 1ha Mudgeeraba block, the design conversation
          opens up &mdash; <strong>freeform pool with curved edges following the
          natural contour</strong>, large baja shelf or sun-deck for kids and
          dogs, integrated spa, beach-entry zero-depth zone, often a
          knife-edge weir falling into a planter on the lower-side topography.
          Concrete is the right material; fibreglass shapes feel constrained
          on these blocks.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">BAL ratings affect the surround &mdash; not the pool.</h3>
        <p>
          Parts of Mudgeeraba (especially the western fringes near the Numinbah
          State Forest and ridgeline blocks) sit in a Bushfire Prone Area under
          Queensland State Planning Policy. <strong>The pool structure itself
          isn&rsquo;t BAL-rated</strong> (concrete and water are non-combustible),
          BUT the surrounding deck, cabana, pool house and pump shed all need to
          meet AS 3959 to the property&rsquo;s BAL level. Most Mudgeeraba blocks
          rate BAL-12.5 to BAL-19; some BAL-29 on west-facing slope blocks. We
          spec the pool surround for compliance from day one.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Pool + cabana combined-build economics.</h3>
        <p>
          Mudgeeraba clients usually want the cabana / pool house as part of the
          same build &mdash; outdoor kitchen, sheltered seating, sometimes a
          guest bedroom + bathroom. Bundling the build saves 15&ndash;25% vs
          doing pool first then cabana separately, mainly through shared site
          establishment, shared coping/paving runs and one set of approvals.
          $60K&ndash;$120K cabana additional to the pool quote.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Mudgeeraba jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>14m freeform concrete pool + 80m&sup2; cabana with kitchen ($250K&ndash;$400K combined)</li>
          <li>Family acreage pool with large baja shelf + integrated spa ($120K&ndash;$180K)</li>
          <li>Existing 1990s acreage pool resurface + new tropical surround ($28K&ndash;$50K)</li>
          <li>BAL-19 compliant pool deck + pool-house combination</li>
          <li>Bore-water-fed pool (common on rural blocks) &mdash; mineral-balance equipment</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mermaid-beach/">Mermaid Beach</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/burleigh-heads/">Burleigh Heads</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/robina/">Robina</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/helensvale/">Helensvale</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/city-of-gold-coast/">All City of Gold Coast</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Mudgeeraba on-site quote.</h2>
        <p>Acreage design language. Granite excavation engineered. Pool + cabana bundle pricing.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
